##A week at a new flower shop on Taobao: Romantic for city dwellers, alive for florists

Wechat. Lucanighttalk

Function description, I want to interview 100 human stories.

The blooming season, which runs from Spring Festival to Valentine's Day and women's Day, has always been the most important trading time for the flower industry in Yunnan.

But this year, the farmers are confused.

The blow to the flower industry has been almost fatal.

Starting Feb. 5, merchants in Yunnan have been throwing away unsold roses in droves.

The DOUNAN flower auction market in Yunnan Province was closed on February 6 and reopened on February 10, but because of traffic control, epidemic prevention and control, this once-bustling flower market, it's the worst Valentine's Day ever.

A total of 3.519 million units were sold at the auction center on Monday, down 41 percent from the same period last year, while the average transaction price for a single unit hit a three-year low, down 70 percent from the same period last year.

This market accounts for more than 70% of the country's fresh cut flower trade.

Many gardeners have no choice but to destroy the flowers day by day when they can not be shipped out.

The first quarter of this year saw a drop of about 842 million flowers traded in Yunnan, according to the report on the impact of the epidemic and snowstorm on the flower industry and enterprises released by the Kunming International Flower Auction and trading center on February 8, transaction volume decreased by about 1.142 billion yuan, together with the input of logistics, agricultural materials and other aspects. The epidemic, together with the recent snow disaster, caused losses of at least 4 billion yuan for the entire flower industry.

Flowers being destroyed

For a while, the news that "one million roses a day have been destroyed" went viral on Weibo, and behind it, many people began to take action.

An overnight flower shop on Taobao is one of them.

On Feb. 10, Hua Gao, who lives in Kunming, posted a message to his friends: The Flower Market, which has just resumed electronic trading, is out of business, exports are suffering, and large numbers of flowers need to find a market. In Hangzhou, Wu Xiaoyi and Gao Huayi have been Internet friends and cat friends for many years. See this message in the friend circle, Wu Xiaoyi asked for help information to his friend circle, also sent to the recent active civil aid volunteer group.

But there were few takers.

Wu Xiaoyi also asked a friend who had opened a flower shop in Beijing. The situation was not optimistic. The friend said that it was too close to Valentine's Day, and it was too late to stock up as a flower shop. Moreover, because of the impact of the epidemic, no one came to the shop, his own business is in the toilet.

People can't go out to the florist. What about the online store?

Guo Guo in the volunteer group raised her hand. She has a vacant Taobao clothing store, which has no decoration and no goods on the shelves. But if all you need to do is make a link to a product, the store is now in good enough condition.

Buyer's show from an enthusiastic buyer

In this way, Wu Xiaoyi put forward the idea of charity sale, fruit out of his empty Taobao shop, Hua Gao is responsible for contact in Kunming flower farmers. A new flower shop is about to open. It just didn't occur to them that it would require a lot more effort on the part of those involved than expected.

On the afternoon of the 11th, after it was confirmed that the local Kunming can still use Shunfeng to deliver the goods, the link of "buy flowers to save farmers" was put on the shelves of Taobao Shop, where fruit has been lying idle for a long time. Wu Xiaoyi self-deprecation says, oneself indescribable became"sell a flower Aunty", hurrying to shout to come to buy a flower in the group.

Wu Xiaoyi and Guo do customer service, responsible for export orders, Hua Gao is responsible for the supply chain in Yunnan.

Hua Gao found one of the farmers, Zheng Wujin, through his connections. He was responsible for contacting a number of flower farmers and sending orders to them every day. The next morning, the farmers picked flowers from the fields and shipped them to Kunming for packing and mailing.

The florist doesn't accept transfers, only cash. Before the first order arrived, Zheng paid the florist in advance for the goods and logistics.

The flower farmers who joined Zheng and Wujin came from two towns in Chuxiong Yi Autonomous Prefecture, Yunnan Province, where about 20,000 mu of flowers had been planted. After the outbreak, a large number of flowers had failed to sell.

Many farmers have borrowed heavily for fertilizer and plants and other early investment, Miss the new year flower trading season, just out of poverty flower farmers are likely to return to poverty due to debt.

The rose variety that ends up in the hands of consumers is Carora, only grade a flowers can go out of the mountains and be sold. Roses below grade a are still being destroyed on the spot by flower growers. A florist in a first-tier city told us that the roses retail for 8-15 yuan, depending on the season.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the flower shop on the shelves of these roses, the final price is 66 yuan 36 + 4, of which + 4 this is logistics wear and tear reserve, if consumers received more than 4 flowers damaged, customer service will follow up compensation. "Our original intention is to help flower farmers open up the market. The cost of operation and logistics is only a rough calculation. It may take a while to figure out how much will be lost. "

Recording list, sorting, packaging, logistics, these are all links that they were not familiar with before.

Although Taobao shop was opened many years ago, the background of Taobao now is no doubt unfamiliar to Wu Xiaoyi. Every day, the team needs to generate a form with batch order information and send it to Kunming. After the courier company returns the flyer number, one by one manual input to Taobao background.

The first 800 orders are so slowly fumbled to complete, until two with e-commerce experience partner with equipment, joined the temporary team. The flower shop is starting to run more efficiently.

Because of local traffic control reasons, logistics often change, some one day can be delivered to the region, the next day can not be issued, can only contact customers refund.

One day, an order from Kunming appeared backstage. The customer left a message saying that there was no need to ship the goods, "I live in Chenggong, where Dou Nan flowers are, " he said. "every day we get flowers from a lot of farmers downstairs in our office. No money, just take them. This time the farmers have lost a lot. I bought this to help them, so I really don't need to send them to me. "

Wu rejected the order, which was essentially a cash donation, because a temporary florist could not afford to complicate matters.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Fresh-picked roses in the flower field

A blogger,@PetitChou  , whom the team had never met, bought the flowers herself and volunteered to help post them on Amway. On the same day, Xiao Zhou's 107-character post was reposted more than 10,000 times. People went to Taobao to search for "buy flowers to save farmers" and found the flower shop to place orders.

The guys at the florist are staring at the big sale backstage.

The team, stunned by the rush of orders, had to take the goods off the shelves temporarily, but Gao received feedback in Kunming that farmers had picked 10,000 flowers that day for sale.

On Weibo, on the other hand, Xiao Zhou faced many questions and comments, and could only explain over and over again. Please be patient.

Confirm good logistics, goods re-shelf, flower shop up and running. Consumers who have already received flowers have sent photos of buyers on Weibo and wechat groups.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Buyer's show

It's been exactly a week since the shop opened, and most of the team members have been friends since then. Wu Xiaoyi and Gao Huayi are cat friends, and fruit is in the group of anti-epidemic volunteers know.

From more than 8,000 orders on the day of the explosion (7,000 actually sold on that day because of logistics restrictions) to an average of more than 2,000 daily sales, the sales of this temporary flower shop for the local unsalable flowers in Yunnan, is still just a drop in the bucket.

"We're just trying to sell as much as we can. " Wu has no plan for how long this will last, but just thinks that if things go well, we can cut down the middle and get better prices for the farmers.

Late on Valentine's Day, finishing the day's order, wu Xiaoyi in the circle of friends wrote a sentence: "The era of a grain of Ash, fall on the head of individuals, is a mountain. And we want to do, but is to join hands with love and kindness to try to hold up this heavy mountain. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Little by little, the impact of the epidemic is showing up in all industries, from material donations to first-line medical and health care workers to the well-intentioned efforts of ordinary people to help farmers launched by major e-commerce platforms, i also give every ordinary you and I strength, prop up the recent days day after day of disappointment, anger and powerlessness.

And Hope for the best.

Friends described the temporary team buying flowers to save the farmers as hot and sensitive, and Wu said her favorite quote was from Albert Camus:

"In the depths of winter, I finally knew I had an unbeatable summer. "
